From 31f2b809fb81292a8d790aebcaec4466ff9bc465 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: reardonia <2925104+reardonia@users.noreply.github.com>
Date: Fri, 8 May 2026 12:59:58 -0400
Subject: [PATCH 24/25] VAAPI: drop libva 1.x compat guards and Vaapi1 interop
 fallback

Drop Vaapi1 support. Remove build-time guards for early Vaapi2
(runtime is still compatible with older Vaapi2 drivers).

CVaapi1Texture (vaDeriveImage interop) is deleted in full;
CVaapi2Texture (vaExportSurfaceHandle) is the only interop path.
Both renderer Register() entry points always select it, and the
per-pixel-format useVaapi2 probe in Configure is gone.

Compile-time guards removed:
  VA_CHECK_VERSION(1, 0, 0)   - libva 2.0.0
  VA_CHECK_VERSION(1, 8, 0)   - libva 2.8.0
  HAVE_VAEXPORTSURFACHEHANDLE - VA_CHECK_VERSION(1, 1, 0) shorthand
  #ifdef VA_RT_FORMAT_*       - 4:2:2 / 4:4:4 / 12-bit RT formats
  #ifdef VA_FOURCC_XYUV
